_json.description: George Whitefield (1714 – September 30, 1770), also known as George Whitfield, was an English Anglican priest who helped spread the Great Awakening in Britain, and especially in the British North American colonies.He was a firm Calvinist in his theology yet unrivaled as an aggressive evangelist. Whitefield preached more than 18,000 sermons in his lifetime, an average of 500 a year or ten a week.
